    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, boil half a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> 'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the dish, breaking it into small chunks and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly dice</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken</strong> to the dish with the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>diced pepper</strong>, <strong>onion wedges </strong>and <strong>crushed garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>with 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven for 40 min or until the potato is tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p><p>When your bake is nearly ready, grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>finely</p><p>Pick the <strong>basil</strong> leaves from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta </strong>into bite-size pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 40 min, remove the dish from the oven and sprinkle over the<strong> grated cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Leave the bake to stand, uncovered, for a final 5 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy chicken, potato & 'Nduja bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>torn ciabatta pieces </strong>to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>finely grated Italian hard cheese </strong>over the top</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy croutons</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-sweet-potato-chicken-bake-with-side/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> spicy 'Nduja & chicken bake</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>cheesy croutons </strong>and <strong>picked basil</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
